 guilty of nameless </div><div class="t m155 x29 h2d yb8e ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">crimes against nature were very common among the </div><div class="t m3be x29 h2d y1548 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">heathen (Rom. 1:27), so much so that many of their • </div><div class="t m195 x29 h2d y9ff ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">wisest philosophers, as Socrates, made no secret of </div><div class="t mb4 x29 h2d y1410 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these crimes, and commended them. There was, </div><div class="t m4d6 x29 h2d y8c8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">therefore, great need of such warning. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
